\h #dBANPLAYER \d

\uUSAGE\n
#dbanplayer \s[\dname reason\s]\d

\uDESCRIPTION\n
Dump the banned player database, or ban/unban a player.
When no arguments are provided, the contents of every record in the database are displayed.
To add a new record to the database (effectively toggling between banned/unbanned status), provide the full PC name of the player you wish to ban/unban, followed by a description of the reason.
If you ban a player who is currently logged in, he/she will be booted immediately.

\uEXAMPLES\n
\q#dbanplayer\d to dump the database.4`
\q#dbanplayer taro for harassment\d to ban Taro.4`
\q#dbanplayer taro the team decided to give him another chance\d to unban Taro.4`

\uSEE ALSO\n
